article.headline: Alabama St. 72, Oakwood 61
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Chief Kickingstallionsims had 14 points to help lead Alabama State to a 72-61 win over Oakwood Wednesday. Alabama State outshot Oakwood 55.3 percent to 38.5 percent. The Hornets also outrebounded the Ambassadors 39-19. With 13 points, forward Brandon Gordon was the only other double figure scorer for the Hornets. Jamarr Sanders helped out with seven assists and Richard Lott, Jr. had nine rebounds. Terrell Black and Dewitt Henley led the Ambassadors with 15 points apiece.
